<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="147" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="147">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="147">
This species may be distinguished from other Canadian 
<taxonomicName authority="Mulsant &amp; Rey, 1873" authorityName="Mulsant &amp; Rey" authorityYear="1873" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Philhygra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Philhygra" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Philhygra</taxonomicName>
by its small subparallel body (length 2.8-3.2 mm), colour dark brown with reddish or yellowish elytra and darker scutellar section, subquadrate pronotum, elytra slightly longer than pronotum, antennal articles V-X subquadrate to slightly elongate (Fig. 21), and distinctive genital structures and terminalia (Figs 22-26).
</paragraph>
